; Declarative wodoc build configuration for wodoc's own documentation site.
; Read by `wodoc build`; replaces doc/build.sh, doc/menu.wiki and the
; doc/gen-manual-nav.py left-navigation script. wodoc dogfoods its own
; turn-key command:
;
;   wodoc build --config doc/wodoc --out _doc-site/<label> \
;               --menu https://ocsigen.org/doc/menu.html --label <label> [--latest] [--local]
;
; `wodoc build` runs `dune build @doc`, assembles every page of the `wodoc`
; package into the Ocsigen site chrome (the shared header from --menu, the
; left navigation generated from (nav ...) below, the version selector) and
; ships the assets. wodoc is a single package with no siblings, so the manual
; here is pure native odoc and no cross-package reference resolution is needed.

(project wodoc)
(title Wodoc)
(pub /wodoc)
(packages wodoc)
(landing wodoc/index.html)

(nav
 (section "Manual"
  (link "Overview" wodoc/index.html index)
  (link "How it works" wodoc/overview.html overview)
  (link "Directives" wodoc/directives.html directives)
  (link "Authoring" wodoc/authoring.html authoring)
  (link "Configuration" wodoc/config.html config)
  (link "Commands" wodoc/commands.html commands)
  (link "Adding a blog" wodoc/blog.html blog))
 (api-section "API"
  (link "API overview" wodoc/api.html api)))
